Package: ParaBAM
Title: C++ Library for multi-threaded sequential reading of short-read aligned
    sequencing BAM files
Version: 0.98.0
Date: 2021-04-22
Authors@R: c(person("Alex Chit Hei", "Wong", email="a.wong@centenary.org.au", 
		role=c("aut", "cre", "cph")))    
Description: C++ header-only library for developers wishing to write software
    to sequentially process BAM files. This package has an advantage over
    Rhtslib in that it supports multi-threaded reading of BAM files using
    OpenMP
License: MIT
Depends:
  R (>= 4.0.0)
Imports:
	Rcpp (>= 1.0.5), zlibbioc, devtools
Suggests: 
    RcppProgress, knitr, rmarkdown, testthat (>= 3.0.0)
VignetteBuilder: knitr
biocViews: Software, Transcriptomics, RNASeq, 
SystemRequirements: C++11
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 7.1.1
URL: https://github.com/alexchwong/ParaBAM
BugReports: https://support.bioconductor.org/
Config/testthat/edition: 3
